:[{"name":"Gregory","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1352858,"age":114,"year":"1519","julianDay":2275863,"description":"Charles I of Spain became Emperor Charles V of the Holy Roman Empire.","jurisdictionLevel":4}],"lifeSummary":"Gregorio Panizzone was born about 1405, in Cortiglione, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Giuliana."},"et":{"about 1405–":"umbes 1405–Surnud","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","1440–1509":"1440–1509","1446–1506":"1446–1506","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1405–Male":"1405–Surnud","1415":"1415","1446":"1446","about 1405":"umbes 1405","1465":"1465","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","1509":"1509","1519":"1519","1506":"1506","about 1450":"umbes 1450","1405":"1405","Hawridge, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hawridge, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Corticella, Piemonte, Italy":"Piemonte, Itaalia","Hawridge":"Hawridge, Buckinghamshire, England","Cortiglione, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy":"Cortiglione, Alessandria, Piemonte, Itaalia","Alessandria, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy":"Alessandria, Alessandria, Piemonte, Itaalia","Piemonte, Massa Martana at Perugia, Umbria, Italy":"Piemonte, Massa Martana, Perugia, Umbria, Itaalia"},"fi":{"abo